                    <comment id="12322050" author="alex+news@olmisoft.com" created="Wed, 1 Dec 2004 21:21:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=13609)&lt;br/&gt;
The patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;public boolean next()&quot; should not modify bucketTable.first when it founds&lt;br/&gt;
matching document, because it is modified in score().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12322051" author="alex+news@olmisoft.com" created="Wed, 1 Dec 2004 21:22:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=13610)&lt;br/&gt;
Test Case to demonstrate the bug&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12322052" author="goller@detego-software.de" created="Sat, 11 Dec 2004 04:41:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the bug. However, I think that the patch is not correct.&lt;br/&gt;
The bug was introduced in the current CVS head by an optimization in&lt;br/&gt;
BooleanScorer. It does not affect the current release. I tried to fix the&lt;br/&gt;
bug. Seems to work. But I am not 100% sure. Another way to fix the bug would be&lt;br/&gt;
to switch off the optimization by simply deleting score(HitCollector hc) and&lt;br/&gt;
score(HitCollector hc, int max) implementation from BooleanScorer. I tried&lt;br/&gt;
this and it works too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Christoph&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
